article.headline: New Hampshire 71, Dartmouth 59
article.story: DURHAM, N.H. (AP) -- Blagoj Janev scored 22 points and grabbed seven rebounds as New Hampshire beat Dartmouth 71-59 Monday night. New Hampshire led by as much as 18 after opening the second period with a 10-2 run led by Jamaal Caterina with five points. Leon Pattman's 3-pointer from the top of the key at 3:42 cut the Wildcat lead to nine points, but a minute later, Jermaine Anderson hit a 3-pointer from the right wing to cushion New Hampshire's lead to 12 points. Dartmouth cut the lead back down to nine points when Michael Giovacchini hit a jumper from the left side at the 40-second mark. Caterina converted a free throw for the Wildcats with 37-seconds remaining to boost New Hampshire with a 10-point advantage (69-59). Vetrano closed the game converting two free throws after a foul was called on Giovacchini. Anderson and Chris Vetrano each contributed 13 points as the Wildcats shot 52 percent from the field. New Hampshire broke open the game in the first half with a 10-point advantage after Vetrano converted a 3-pointer from the right wing at 8:01. New Hampshire held a 34-20 advantage at the half.
